{
  "texts": [
    "Achieving the optimal balance is inherently challenging.",
    "Nevertheless, no successful intervention that assessed safety outcomes in our review has led to a deterioration in patient safety (Table 1).",
    "Although we cannot exclude publication bias, it is a strong argument in advocating for inappropriate tests reduction.A major challenge in interpreting data from these interventions is the overall poor quality of design, lack of standardization in methodology and diversity of outcomes [23,27,30,104].",
    "Table 3 summarizes various confounding factors that explain this heterogeneity.",
    "For example, studies have shown that size (reflected by the number of involved healthcare workers) is a significant confounding factor for the effectiveness of an intervention [119]."
  ]
}